column18:
The purpose of this research study is to understand decision-making behaviors in a strategic setting.
The study consists of 3 parts, in the following order:
 1. a short survey
 2. a decision-making task (with performance-based monetary reward)
 3. a second short survey.

The two surveys include questions about your demographic information, traits and your opinions about the decision-making task.
Completing the entire study will take about 20-30 minutes.
